{
  "attrs": {
    "abstract": "This dataset provides a Climate Data Record of Sea Ice Thickness for the northern hemisphere polar region, derived from the RA (Radar Altimeter) instrument on the ERS-2 satellite (European Remote-sensing Satellite - 2). This product was generated in the context of the ESA Climate Change Initiative Programme (ESA CCI) by the Sea Ice CCI (Sea_Ice_cci) project.\n\nIt provides daily sea ice thickness data for the months October to April annually on the satellite measurement grid (Level 2P) at the full sensor resolution for the period October 1995 to April 2003.",
    "catalog_url": "https://catalogue.ceda.ac.uk/uuid/17c6b09a5466406c800c2978f17b8372",
    "cci_project": "SEAICE",
    "comment": "Northern hemisphere sea ice thickness coverage is limited to the winter month between October and April due to negative effect of surface melt on the retrieval of freeboard. Please consult the Product User Guide (PUG) for more information.",
